This paper deals with influence spreading in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and social sciences. The paper presents theoretical methods and algorithms for measuring and eliminating redundant influence in order to maximize spreading influence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
